    "hint.dismiss": "GOT IT",
    "hint.k1_01_erste_gleise": "Click and drag on the grid to lay track, from the source to the destination. Wrong spot? Remove a piece with B (eraser) or a right-click.",
    "hint.k1_02_um_das_hindernis": "R and T rotate the track piece, right-click opens the curve shapes. Every segment costs material, so find the short way around the obstacle.",
    "hint.k1_03_bloeke_und_signale": "A block signal (3) holds a train while the section behind it is occupied. Place one before the crossing so two trains never enter it at once.",
    "hint.k1_04_verwindende_strecke": "The trick is the loop: build, press start, watch where it jams, back to the editor, fix it. A crash shows you exactly where and why.",
    "hint.k1_05_weichen": "Build a switch with key 2. Then press Q, click the switch, and pick the right exit per destination. The switch decides where a train turns.",
    "hint.k1_06_weichen_und_signale": "Rule of thumb: switches decide WHERE a train goes, signals WHEN. Combine both to route several trains to the right place without conflict.",
    "hint.k1_07_ausweichgleis": "A passing siding: two switches in and back out, a signal between them. One train waits on the side track while the other passes.",
    "hint.k1_09_blockchaos": "A chain signal (4) holds a train BEFORE the crossing until the whole path beyond is clear, so no one ever stalls in the middle of a junction. That is what prevents deadlocks.",
    "hint.k1_10_durch_das_tal": "Improving one score often costs another, throughput versus material. Solve it safely first, then rebuild toward a specific medal.",
    "result.success": "TIMETABLE FULFILLED",
    "result.collision": "COLLISION",
