    "tool.block": "Block",
    "tool.select.desc": "Selects a switch or signal to open its configuration panel (signals: merge priority). Places nothing itself.",
    "tool.track.desc": "Connects two connectors of a cell. Drag to draw a whole line, or click to place the current form. Building over your own track or switches replaces them automatically. R/T rotate the form by 45°, right-click opens the direction menu for curves.",
    "tool.switch.desc": "Steers trains onto one of two branches. Clicking over your own track or switches replaces them. The config panel sets the default branch and rules per destination or train class — only reachable destinations are offered.",
    "tool.signal_block.desc": "Cuts the track net into blocks. A train enters a block only when it is clear. The arrow shows the guarded travel direction; R/T pick it.",
    "tool.signal_chain.desc": "Like the block signal, but also reserves the next block ahead — so trains do not deadlock each other at crossings.",
    "tool.erase.desc": "Removes the red-highlighted element under the cursor: track, switches and signals (in the sandbox also blocks, sources and sinks). Drag to wipe a whole stroke. Level-fixed track cannot be demolished.",
    "tool.source.desc": "(Sandbox) Places a train source on a connector. Trains depart here per the timetable.",
    "tool.sink.desc": "(Sandbox) Places a destination on a connector. A train counts as arrived once it reaches it.",
    "tool.block.desc": "(Sandbox) Blocks an empty cell: nothing can be built there and it shows as a dark block. Drag to block several cells; click a block to clear it again.",
    "help.button": "TOOL HELP",
    "help.title": "TOOLS",
    "help.intro": "An overview of every build tool. (Later: an encyclopedia with images and videos.)",
    "help.controls": "Controls: 1–4 tools · Q select · B demolish · 5–7 sandbox (block/source/sink) · tool rail on the left is clickable · R/T rotate · right-click track direction menu · Ctrl+Z/Y undo/redo",
